# Safety invariants (non-negotiable)

Carried from v1; enforced in code review, contracts, and tests.

## Model boundary

```
Claude (strategic) ← Mistral (orchestration) → Groq (compile)
════════════════ MODEL-FREE BELOW COMPILE ════════════════
deterministic gates → dispatch → broker → verification
```

- **Groq compile is the LAST model-bearing stage.** Never add LLM calls below it.
- Dispatch and verification are **model-free and provider-free**.

## Guardrails & verification

- Guardrail packages and verification schemas: **immutable at runtime**
- Only **weights** and **bounded-range positions** inside envelopes are mutable
- Fail-closed on out-of-scope/out-of-range/unknown levers (`enforceScopeStrict`)

## Paper / live parity

- One engine; mode changes adapters, limits, compliance paths only
- **Live is fail-closed** until explicit gates pass (`plans/master-build-plan.md`)
- Never enable live-trading without documented gate criteria

## Paper experiment runs

Fail-closed abort if any of:

- Company mode is not `paper` for the experiment cohort
- Live broker adapter or live credentials used on the experiment dispatch path
- Live gate bypassed or live master switch enabled without documented gate pass

Use `.cursor/skills/paper-experiment/SKILL.md` and `agent-docs/research/paper-experimentation-protocol.md`.

## Numbers and time (D-008, D-009)

- LLMs never read/write/transform raw financial numbers or authoritative dates/times/durations
- Flow: live source / clock / calendar → ValueRef → calculator → levers → execution
- Leak lint all model outputs (digits + datetime patterns); sanity checks at every morph
- Timestamps OK as **read-only orientation context** only

## Compliance copy

- No guaranteed-returns language in code, docs, or UI
- Entitlement truthfulness; session legality; text-first status (color reinforces only)

Full detail: `AGENTS.md`, `architecture/number-handling.md`, `architecture/llm-pipeline.md`.
